        <abstract> 
<p>Describes his brother Alexander’s discovery of male of <hi rend="italic">Bonellia</hi>, a striking example of dimorphism. Encloses a plate with notes on his brother’s work.</p> 
            <p>The difficulty his wife, Sofya Kovalevsky, has had as a woman in being admitted to Berlin University. Kirchow [Gustav Robert Kirchhoff], at Heidelberg, has taken an interest in her.</p>
        </abstract>
